{"parse":{"title":"Lament of the Holy Cross","pageid":43163611,"revid":842206954,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b>Lament of the Holy Cross</b> (Polish: <b>Lament swietokrzyski</b>) is a medieval Polish <a href=\"/wiki/Planctus\" title=\"Planctus\">planctus</a>, written by unknown author probably in late 15th century. It now is regarded as one of lyrical masterpieces of the era. Literary historians emphasize the fact that the Lament presents <a href=\"/wiki/Mary_(mother_of_Jesus)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Mary (mother of Jesus)\">Mary</a> almost as a human being, with feelings and emotions. Most likely, the text used to be part of the <a href=\"/wiki/Good_Friday\" title=\"Good Friday\">Good Friday</a> mysterium. \n</p><p>Lament of the Holy Cross is the monologue of Mary, who is painful and mourns her son <a href=\"/wiki/Jesus_Christ\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Jesus Christ\">Jesus Christ</a>, standing under his cross. At first, she calls on people standing around her, urging them to show compassion and understanding. She then turns to her son, hoping to ease his sufferings and get closer to him. Later Mary gets angry and rebellious, and the text is completed with an appeal to all mothers to pray to God for their sons. \n</p><p>The Lament comes from the Benedictine Monastery at <a href=\"/wiki/Lysa_Gora\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Lysa Gora\">Lysa Gora</a> in the <a href=\"/wiki/Holy_Cross_Mountains\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Holy Cross Mountains\">Holy Cross Mountains</a>, and was probably written in ca. 1470. \n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Lament_of_the_Holy_Cross&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Old_Polish_language\" title=\"Old Polish language\">Old Polish language</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Sources\">Sources</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Lament_of_the_Holy_Cross&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Sources\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li>Poezja polska XIV - XV wieku. W: Tadeusz Witczak: Literatura \u015aredniowiecza. Warszawa: Polskie Wydawnictwo Naukowe, 2002</li></ul>\n<p><br />\n</p>\n<table class=\"metadata plainlinks stub\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"background:transparent\"><tbody><tr><td><span style=\"vertical-align: middle; background:transparent\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Flag_of_Poland.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Flag of Poland\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/1/12/Flag_of_Poland.svg/30px-Flag_of_Poland.svg.png\" width=\"30\" height=\"19\" class=\"thumbborder\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/1/12/Flag_of_Poland.svg/45px-Flag_of_Poland.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/1/12/Flag_of_Poland.svg/60px-Flag_of_Poland.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"1280\" data-file-height=\"800\" /></a><span style=\"margin-left:-30px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Hourglass_drawing.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Hourglass icon\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c2/Hourglass_drawing.svg/23px-Hourglass_drawing.svg.png\" width=\"23\" height=\"30\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c2/Hourglass_drawing.svg/35px-Hourglass_drawing.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c2/Hourglass_drawing.svg/46px-Hourglass_drawing.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"546\" data-file-height=\"708\" /></a></span></span>&#160;&#160;</td><td><i>This <a href=\"/wiki/History_of_Poland\" title=\"History of Poland\">Polish history</a>\u2013related article is a <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Stub\" title=\"Wikipedia:Stub\">stub</a>. You can help Wikipedia by <a class=\"external te